DECEMBER 9, 1999 | Professor Schultz talked about his book The Secret War Against Hanoi: Kennedy and Johnson’s Use of Spies, Saboteurs, and Covert Warriors in North Vietnam, published by Harper Collins. Professor Schultz was a member of the covert operations team, the “Studies and Observation Group” from 1964 to 1972 during the Vietnam War. The book describes psychological operations, commando raids, espionage, and deception operations. He specifically talked about President Kennedy taking the covert actions projects away from the CIA and turning them over to the Studies Observation Group.

